HEADWORD: Reclamation
<hw>Rec`la*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧k`l⟦adot⟧*m⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧clamation</ets>, L.
<ets>reclamatio</ets>. See <er>Reclaim</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act or process of reclaiming.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Representation made in opposition;
remonstrance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would now, on the <qex>reclamation</qex> both of generosity and
of justice, try clemency.</q> <rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

